## DESIGN CONSTRAINTS

- Two-pane sidebar on landscape/tablet exactly like GameHub screenshots
- Sidebar width: 200dp, gnBgSurface background, gnDivider right border
- Selected sidebar item: gnAccentSubtle background, 3dp gnAccentPrimary left accent bar
- All settings rows: standard height 52-56dp, chevron icon on right
- Current value shown right of chevron in gnTextSecondary
- Section dividers between rows: gnDivider color, 0.5dp height
- Bottom Launch button: always pinned above navigation bar, gnAccentPrimary fill
- Cannot-run screen: shown INSTEAD of settings when hard blockers exist, with "Open Settings Anyway" escape hatch for advanced users
- Recommendation banner: always at top of General and Compatibility panels, dismissable
- FPS counter in top bar (gnNeonTeal) when game is running — matches GameHub UI
- Compatibility Layer picker: show all available versions with RECOMMENDED badge on auto-selected
- Component screen: show installed size, active badge, download/remove buttons
- No new colors — only existing gn_* tokens
- Fonts: GameNativeFontFamily (Outfit) via PluviaTypography everywhere
- All hardware reads and config saves on Dispatchers.IO
- Config persisted to GameProfileStore on every change (no explicit save button needed)
